    There are a lot of columns here having more null values than non-null
values and I don't even think if these columns will be of any use when
it comes to conducting analysis or visualisations. Features like
in\_reply\_to\_status\_id, in\_reply\_to\_user\_id,
retweeted\_status\_id, retweeted\_status\_user\_id aren't of much use
here since all of them act as unique identifiers and we already have the
tweet id column as the primary key here. This is actually a tidiness
issue since these columns aren't really needed.

Also, tweet\_id should be a string instead of an integer since I want it
to be a primary key and anyways we won't be doing any calculations with
it. The data type for the timestamp column should be datetime instead of
string.

    On checking out the duplicated values in the name feature its evident
that maybe a lot of the dogs didn't have a name or that data got lost
and got replaced by the default 'None'. Also there are a lot of
irrelevant values in that column like 'a', 'quite', 'the' which clearly
shows that the wrong text was extracted from the text column. This issue
should come under the accuracy dimension of quality issues.

Also, the url for the tweet with tweet id 885518971528720385 seems to be
broken as the page cannot be found.

    \subsubsection{Quality}\label{quality}

\paragraph{Twitter archives table}\label{twitter-archives-table}

\begin{itemize}
\tightlist
\item
  Most of the values in the in\_reply\_to\_status\_id,
  in\_reply\_to\_user\_id, retweeted\_status\_id,
  retweeted\_status\_user\_id and retweeted\_status\_timestamp columns
  are null and these columns only act as identifiers.
\item
  Missing records in the expanded\_urls column (2297 out of 2356).
\item
  Retweets in many rows.
\item
  Incorrect data types for tweet\_id, timestamp and rating\_numerator.
\item
  Inaccurate dog names in the name column and NaN values represented by
  the word 'None'.
\item
  Inaccurate values in the rating\_numerator and rating\_denominator
  columns.
\item
  The source column is a bit untidy cause of the urls and thus a little
  difficult to interpret.
\item
  The tweet with the dog name Phineas has been duplicated.
\end{itemize}

\paragraph{Image predictions table}\label{image-predictions-table}

\begin{itemize}
\tightlist
\item
  Incorrect data type for tweet id.
\item
  Underscores in place of spaces in the p1, p2, p3 prediction columns.
\item
  The values in the columns p1\_conf, p2\_conf and p3\_conf should be

    \subsubsection{Define}\label{define}

Do an inner join on this table and the image\_predictions table since we
only want tweets with images and no retweets. Also, drop the unnecessary
columns after that. This will also remove all the rows with null values
in the expanded\_urls column since those are the tweets with no images
and thus aren't there in the image predictions table.

    \subsubsection{Define}\label{define}

Replace the incorrect dog names i.e. the names in lowercases with the
correct ones by extracting them from their corresponding text. Also
replace the remaining 'None' in the name column by NaN values.

                                                       \PY{n}{twitter\PYZus{}archives\PYZus{}clean}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{name}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{str}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{islower}\PY{p}{(}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{]}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{index}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{tolist}\PY{p}{(}\PY{p}{)}

         \PY{k}{for} \PY{n}{e} \PY{o+ow}{in} \PY{n}{all\PYZus{}indices}\PY{p}{:}
             \PY{k}{if} \PY{n}{e} \PY{o+ow}{in} \PY{n}{index\PYZus{}list}\PY{p}{:}
                 \PY{k}{for} \PY{n}{ele} \PY{o+ow}{in} \PY{n+nb}{list}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n+nb}{range}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n+nb}{len}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{index\PYZus{}list}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{:}
                     \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{}creating a list out of all such text values that contain the word \PYZsq{}named\PYZsq{} and the corresponding name value }
                     \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{}is in lowercase            }
                     \PY{n}{text\PYZus{}list} \PY{o}{=} \PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{twitter\PYZus{}archives\PYZus{}clean}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{loc}\PY{p}{[}\PY{n}{twitter\PYZus{}archives\PYZus{}clean}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{text}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{str}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{contains}\PY{p}{(}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{l+s+s1}{named}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{p}{)} \PY{o}{\PYZam{}}
